<fragment>
  <heading level="2">Whales</heading>
  <list>
    <item>Blue whales are the largest animals to have ever existed on Earth.
      <list>
        <item>A blue whale's heart is the size of a small car and can be heard beating from two miles away.</item>
        <item>Blue whales can consume up to 4 tons of krill in a single day.</item>
      </list>
    </item>
    <item>Humpback whales are known for their complex songs that can last for hours.</item>
    <item>Beluga whales are called "sea canaries" because of their vocal and chatty nature.</item>
  </list>
</fragment>